  "raw_response": "{\n  \"title\": \"Gold 4H Reaccumulation Using Old Bearish Order Blocks as Mitigation Zones After Smart Money Reversal\",\n  \"school\": \"ICT\",\n  \"asset\": \"XAUUSD\",\n  \"timeframe\": \"4H\",\n  \"market_context\": \"After a smart money reversal confirmed by a market structure shift and displacement higher, price retraced into old bearish order blocks from the prior sell-side phase. The analyst identified these as mitigation blocks for reaccumulation within an uptrend.\",\n  \"key_observation\": \"Price reacted strongly at retested old bearish order blocks (mitigation blocks) after the smart money reversal, using them as support to continue higher—confirmed by SMT divergence with another asset.\",\n  \"analysis_steps\": [\n    \"Step 1: Identify the weekly fair value gap as the higher time frame point of interest and confirm a market structure shift (BOS) with displacement higher.\",\n    \"Step 2: Locate old bearish order blocks on the left side of the chart (sell side of the curve) formed by up-close candles into key levels before the new low.\",\n    \"Step 3: Drag those old bearish order blocks forward as mitigation blocks to anticipate reaccumulation zones in the new bullish phase.\",\n    \"Step 4: Wait for price to retest the mitigation block; observe reaction (e.g., rejection wick, close above mean threshold) and confirm with SMT divergence for added confidence.\",\n    \"Step 5: Enter long on retest of the mitigation block, targeting the original consolidation high or next HTF liquidity level.\"\n  ],\n  \"outc",
